# Cursor Rules — @forgesworn/shamir-words

TypeScript library for Shamir's Secret Sharing over GF(256) with BIP-39 word encoding.

## Commands

```bash
npm install
npm run build      # tsc → dist/
npm test           # vitest run
npm run typecheck  # tsc --noEmit
```

## Conventions

- British English in docs and comments — licence, serialise, colour
- ESM-only (`"type": "module"`) — no CommonJS
- Strict TypeScript — `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` enabled
- TDD — write tests before implementation changes
- Commit format: `type: description` (e.g. `fix:`, `feat:`, `refactor:`)
- No `Co-Authored-By` lines in commits
- Zero secrets in memory — use `zeroBytes` after polynomial coefficient use
- Audited deps only — `@noble/hashes` and `@scure/bip39`; no homebrew crypto

## Key Patterns

- GF(256) arithmetic — field operations used for Shamir polynomial evaluation
- BIP-39 word encoding — shares serialised as 11-bit groups mapped to wordlist
- Wire format v2 — `[data_length, threshold, share_id, ...data, checksum]` → words
- Share IDs are 1-indexed (1–255) — 0 is not a valid GF(256) evaluation point
- Secret max 255 bytes — single-byte length prefix limits wire format
- Error hierarchy — `ShamirError` → `ShamirValidationError` / `ShamirCryptoError`

## Structure

- `src/index.ts` — entire library (GF arithmetic, split/reconstruct, encoding)
- `tests/index.test.ts` — comprehensive vitest suite
- `dist/` — compiled output (committed; rebuilt by CI)
